gomodel:SYNGO_1473  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Brevican is perisynaptic at excitatory and inhibitory synapses of primary hippocampal cultures (after 21 days in vitro).\n\n13/10/2017 Pim\n- This annotation does not show the localization to the synaptic cleft/perisynaptic space perse, but shows co-localization with GABAergic and Glutamatergic synapses in cultured hippocampal neurons. The localization of brevican of to the ECM in inferred from previous data and author intent.. Experimental description: \"Hippocampal cultures from 18-day-old embryonic rats were prepared and grown on cover slips\" p. 782" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
